      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>The Hotline, the popular Internet political tip sheet, keeps a running tab of presidential preference polls in various states as they become available. Last week, six new polls were added. Here is how things stood over all when everything had been voted up:</p>
        <p>Gov. George W. Bush led in 24 states, worth 263 electoral votes. Vice President Al Gore led in 9 states, worth 157 electoral votes.</p>
        <p>Needed to win: 270 electoral votes.</p>
      </block>
